wdi-BX.TRF.CURR.CD.def: Secondary income refers to transfers recorded in the balance of payments whenever an economy provides or receives goods, services, income, or financial items without a quid pro quo. All transfers not considered to be capital are current. Data are in current U.S. dollars.
wdi-BX.TRF.CURR.CD.name: Secondary income receipts
wdi-BX.TRF.CURR.CD.source: International Monetary Fund, Balance of Payments Statistics Yearbook and data files.
